01/12/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Visiting Sarajevo on Thursday (November 30th), Croatian President Stipe Mesic met with the three members of the BiH presidency and urged the country to boost co-operation with the UN war crimes tribunal and meet its obligations to the international community.
Mesic added that by boosting bilateral co-operation, BiH and Croatia would finally convince the EU and the international community that the region is secure, stable and worthy of foreign investment.
(Fena, HINA - 30/11/06)
